  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={1-3},
  abstract={In order to improve the Quality of Service (QoS) of the network, a computational system has been proposed to perform decision making based on network quality by receiving network information such as network throughput, packet loss rate and delay. The system as a whole verifies whether or not the use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) is required to improve network quality and coverage of the most demanding area. If UAVs are required, they will be moved to these areas of greatest demand; otherwise, the UAVs will remain at the base station. Using the proposed method, there were significant improvements in network QoS, allowing for a reduction in packet loss and delay and an increase in network throughput rate.},
